rooms.Name: A room of spikes and sharp protrusions
rooms.Description:
You are in pain as the blades and spikes from all sides of this room cut
into your soft flesh.  Your eyes are pierced by the sharp spikes when you
try to avoid some of the more sharper blades next to you.  The pain is
excruciating as you feel your bowels are about to spill from your exposed
stomach.  You choke in your own blood as one of the jagged blades rip open
your throat.
Sorry, young traveler, your long journey ends here and now.

Exits.Description: Behind this secret entrance is a hallway to somewhere...

rooms.Name: Inside a dark hallway
rooms.Description:
It's dark and you're afraid.  You're afraid of what's inside this dark
corridor which will take you to the bloodthirsty warlord named Dragomir.
As you walk along this passageway, you can smell the fresh blood dripping
from the walls and ceiling.  The hallway seems to be sloping downwards and
it's too bad you can't see where it leads to...probably a deathtrap!

Exits.Description: This exit will take you back to the corridor outside.

rooms.Name: Inside a dark hallway
rooms.Description:
It's still dark and there's no way you can see where you're going.  You
sense Lord Dragomir is watching your every movement as you try finding your
way around this darkness maze.  Only one with the strong sense or (skill)
may find the location he is searching for.

Exits.Description:
There's a strange trapdoor on the ground...hmmm, wonder if that's the door
to Dragomir's domain?

rooms.Name: Lord Dragomir's Bedroom
rooms.Description:
This room is unlike all the other rooms you've been in.  The decorations
here are simply incredible even though they are simple and unpretentious.
Though you can't see this entire room from a giant's view, you can sense it
belongs to someone of great importance.  That someone is here, and he's
towering over you with closed fists.  He looks angry and at the same time
surprised that you would dare come inside his royal bedroom.  You sense
Lord Dragomir is about to DEMOLISH you from where you stand and there
doesn't see to be anywhere to you...you are trapped!

Exits.Description:
This is your way out of here without having to go into a DT...but as you
try pulling the handle of this massive door, you find out that it's been
locked tight!  You are stuck in this room with Lord Dragomir unless you
can find the key to open this darn door!
Only a fool will go into this DT!

rooms.Name: Ragnarok's enchanted prison cell
rooms.Description:
Standing before you is the tallest giant you have ever seen.  He stands
next to a lovely giantess in a mammoth fur cloak.  The male giant is bulky
and strong.  The armors that cover his entire body make him look regal as
well as fearsome.  His long white beard suggests that he has been here for
hundreds of years, maybe even centuries.  But even though, he may look old
and tired, he's still bigger and stronger than most giants inside this 
great fortress.

rooms.Name: An enchanted prison cell
rooms.Description:
You feel a strange wave of energy passing through you as you walk inside
this dark cell.  This looks to be a prison cell of some sort and it seems
someone went through a lot of trouble trying to keep whatever's in here
inside this confined room.

Exits.Description: This cell door will take you back to the hallway which you came.

rooms.Name: Inside a secret passageway
rooms.Description:
As you walk into this section of the tunnel, your feet is trapped by the
sticky cobwebs on the floor!  You can't move at all!  As you struggle to
free yourself from this trap, you notice a giant spider is coming towards
you.  It's drooling green acid and it looks hungry for blood...your blood!
There's nowhere you can run, this spider will be fed tonight no matter how
hard you try to fight it.

Exits.Description: Behind this door is a secret kept for a thousand years!

rooms.Name: Inside a secret passageway
rooms.Description:
Only a giant would think that this passageway is too narrow to pass
through, but for a human, there's enough room to move a truck inside.  This
tunnel looks dark and creepy.  You wonder what could be hiding inside this
hallway...could there be a large treasure somewhere around here?

Exits.Description: This exit will take you back to the DT!!!!

rooms.Name: The end of the corridor inside the Fortress
rooms.Description:
Finally, you reach the end of the hallway.  This section of the corridor
looks to lead you towards a room, east of here.  The door is made of a
strange polished metal and it's locked tight.  There are some inscriptions
on the door that looks like a warning of some kind.

Exits.Description:
This door is impossible to break into...the room behind it must belong to
a great king or a leader.

ExtraDescs.Description:
Please Do Not Disturb!  This is the room of our sire, Lord Dragomir,
leader and warrior supreme of the Frost Giants.  Whoever dares to disturb
his lordship will be severely punished!

rooms.Name: The corridor inside the Fortress
rooms.Description:
There seems to be no end to this hallway as you struggle to reach your
destination point.  As you continue your long journey in this fortress, the
tremors caused by the footsteps are still around you.  The giant walking
along this hallway must be somewhere near you...

rooms.Name: The corridor inside the Fortress
rooms.Description:
The long journey of this mile long stretch of hallway is torturous.  You
can still feel the footsteps of a giant coming closer and closer to you,
but you're not sure where he is right at this moment.  To the west, there's
a massive door that'll take you inside a room.

Exits.Description: A sign in front of the door reads, 'Brachio's Trophy Room.'

rooms.Name: Brachio's Trophy Room
rooms.Description:
This room is a taxidermist's dream.  There are hundreds and maybe thousands
of animal heads mounted on the walls.  Skins and bones of these rare
animals are placed on shelves as decorative pieces in this room.  A giant
is here, sitting on his elk-horned, bear skin chair.  He's sharpening his
arrowheads so he could prepare himself for another hunting trip.

Exits.Description: This exit will take you back to the corridor outside.

rooms.Name: Kronos' Arsenal Chamber
rooms.Description:
This room is just filled with weapons of all different types.  From wall to
wall and from display cases to trophy stands, there are ancient weapons
sitting there for exhibition.  Standing in the middle of the room, is a
giant, wielding a powerful weapon of destruction and practicing his
fighting technique.  This giant is so big and so powerful, he looks like he
could solo an entire viking army.

Exits.Description: This exit will take you back to the corridor outside of here.

rooms.Name: Lykos' Kitchen
rooms.Description:
The first thing you notice upon entering this room, are the cooking utensils
and the oversized kitchen appliances.  This must be where the giants cook
their daily meals.  As you turn your head to a kitchen counter, you notice
a giant is there skinning a catch from the day's hunt.  It looks like a 
large chicken that he's butchering, but upon a closer inspection, you can
see he's cutting up a human carcass!

Exits.Description: This exit will take you back to the Fortress' corridor.

rooms.Name: The east corridor inside the Fortress
rooms.Description:
You are tired of running from the monsters that live inside this mammoth
fortress.  The corridors are miles long and you short legs are no help to
you in your struggle to reach your destination point.  To the east, there's
a door that'll take you inside a private room.

Exits.Description: A sign in of the door reads, 'Lyko's Kitchen.'

rooms.Name: Zbysko's Library
rooms.Description:
You are in awe to see so many books on the shelves and the floor.  This
room is just packed with leather-bound books and ancient scrolls.  As you
look around this crowded room, you notice a giant is sitting on the corner
table.  He looks very busy, studying a brittle scroll.  You probably don't
want to disturb this studious giant...for he could squash you like a bug
if he so wishes to.

Exits.Description: This exit will take you back to the corridor of this Fortress.

rooms.Name: The east corridor inside the Fortress
rooms.Description:
As soon as you enter this section of the hallway, you sense someone or
something is watching you.  Suddenly, you feel you're in danger as the
sounds come closer to you.  There's a large door to the north of where
you're standing and the corridor continues to the south of here.

Exits.Description: A sign in front of this door reads, 'Zbysko's Library.'

rooms.Name: The east corridor inside the Fortress
rooms.Description:
Darkness begins to surround you as the hallway torches slowly burn out.  
As you walk along this long corridor, you can hear an odd sound...  It
sounds like an animal of some sort, with claws and a blood-curdling squeak.
You are afraid even to find out what it is but if you're curious to know,
the animal is just east of here.

rooms.Name: The east corridor inside the Fortress
rooms.Description:
This hallway is much more dimmer than the other sections of this continuous
corridor.  In fact, it's so dark, you could barely see the direction you're
headed.  The hallway torches look as though they're about to burn out any
moment and there's no one here to replace them.

rooms.Name: The corridor inside the Fortress
rooms.Description:
Is there no end to this corridor, you think to yourself.  The further you
walk along this hallway, the more it seems to get longer and longer.  To
the west of here, there's a large door that'll take you inside a room and
to the east, you see another intersecting corridor that'll take you to the
east wing of this mammoth fortress.

Exits.Description: The sign in front of this door reads, 'Kronos' Arsenal Chamber.'

rooms.Name: The corridor inside the Fortress
rooms.Description:
It's impossible to see where this long hallway will end unless you're about
sixty feet tall.  You sense there's someone headed to your direction and
they should be here any moment.  There's nowhere to hid in this corridor
so your only option is to run!

rooms.Name: Titano's Torture Chamber
rooms.Description:
From wall to wall, you can see blood splattered all over this place.  This
is where the bloodthirsty inhabitants of this fortress bring their defeated
enemies.  As you walk inside this room, you can smell the putrid odor of
decaying flesh and it's almost impossible to bear.  In the corner of the
room, there's a giant there adjusting the stretcher on one of his many
victims.  He doesn't seem to know your presence so make sure you don't let
him know you're here...

Exits.Description: This exit will take you back to the Fortress' corridor.

rooms.Name: The corridor inside the Fortress
rooms.Description:
This is not an earthquake you're feeling on the ground, it's more like
footsteps of a giant creature!  It seems to be heading to your direction
and unless you make yourself scarce, who knows what the inhabitants of this
fortress will do to intruders.  To the southeast of here, you see a very
large door that'll take you into a room.

Exits.Description: A sign in front of this door reads, 'Titano's Torture Chamber.'

rooms.Name: Nuklo's Combat Room
rooms.Description:
This entire room is decorated with ancient weapons and battle armors of all
kinds.  In a center of this room, there's a large padded mat and standing
on top of it, is a large muscle-bound giant.  You cringe in fear as this
monster towers over you with his arms raised.  He seems to be gesturing you
to do battle with him...

Exits.Description: This exit will take you back to the Fortress' corridor.

rooms.Name: The corridor inside the Fortress
rooms.Description:
The floors are shaking very hard but it doesn't feel like any earthquake
you experienced.  It feels more like footsteps...giant footsteps...heading
towards your direction!  You are in trouble now and you have no idea where
to go and hide.  To the southwest, there's a large door that'll take you
into a room of some sort.

Exits.Description: A sign in front of this door reads, 'Nuklo's Combat Room.'

rooms.Name: The corridor inside the Fortress
rooms.Description:
You wish you were about fifty feet taller so that you can move around this
place more quickly.  This hallway seems to be splitting into two sections,
one heading northwest and the other, northeast.  As you continue walking
along this corridor, you could feel the floor moving as though an earthquake
was happening right at this moment.

rooms.Name: Inside the Fortress of the Frost Giants
rooms.Description:
There are no words to describe the interior of this oversized building.
From corner to corner, everything here seems to be ten times the size of
normal.  You can't imagine who could be living inside this fortress...
maybe it could be a family of giants like the one guarding the outside
entrance.  You are tempted to explore this area further, and there's a
corridor to your north which will take you all around this place.

Exits.Description: This exit will take you back outside of this Fortress!

rooms.Name: The doorway to the Frost Giants' Fortress
rooms.Description:
This massive door to the north of you is one of the things that block you
from going inside this building.  The other thing is the giant that stands
in your way.  Armed with spiked battle gear, a bladed shield, and a bone-
crushing mace, the monster looks ready to mutilate anyone trying to pass
through this doorway.  He stares at you with a taunting expression and you
hesitate to even try to attack this juggernaut.

Exits.Description: This door will take you inside the Fortress of the Frost Giants!

rooms.Name: On a snowy trail
rooms.Description:
You are in awe to see this large building that's built in the middle of
nowhere.  You didn't expect to find anything around this entire region
except for small creatures and some vegetation.  As you look around this
colossal building, you'll notice it's shaped like an ancient cabin except
that it's the size of a grand castle.  As you focus your eyes to the
doorway of this fortress, you are astonished to see a giant is standing 
there and guarding the entrance.

rooms.Name: On a snowy trail
rooms.Description:
The weather in this region is cold and dry.  Your constant shivering and
your teeth chattering is a distraction to your concentration as you try to
focus on reaching your destination.  As you continue your journey 
northward, you'll notice a large construct is built to that direction.

rooms.Name: On a snowy trail
rooms.Description:
You are tired and in need of a rest but there's nowhere you can lie down
on.  Almost everything you see is covered in a thick bed of snow except for
the tall trees around you.  If you continue your journey, you feel you
might die of exhaustion before you reach your destination point.

rooms.Name: On a snowy trail
rooms.Description:
The thick bed of snow beneath your waist is numbing your legs quickly.  You
hardly feel your legs as you struggle to concentrate on the journey.  The
climate of this region looks pretty fair and there doesn't seem to be any
signs of a blizzard storm coming.

rooms.Name: The Great Mountain of Norn
rooms.Description:
The loose rocks on the sides of this mountain make it almost impossible to
get a firm gripping.  You feel you're about to slip off this mountain and
fall to your death.  Also the horrible windy conditions of this altitude
isn't helping your predicament.

rooms.Name: The Great Mountain of Norn
rooms.Description:
There's nothing living around this area except for some small vegetation
growing inside the crevices.  There are also tiny mushrooms sprouting out
of the loose stones and you wonder if they're edible or not.  There is
still a long climb ahead of you and you notice the windy weather up here 
is getting worse.

rooms.Name: The Great Mountain of Norn
rooms.Description:
You finally find a ledge that you can rest on, but it's only a small ledge
and you can't lie down on it.  As you sit down to rest your tired body, you
look around this amazing landscape with fascination and awe.  You didn't
know how beautiful the surroundings are on this side of the mountain because
you were too busy concentrating on climbing this mammoth rock.

rooms.Name: The Great Mountain of Norn
rooms.Description:
The altitude of this great mountain is making it hard to breathe.  You
gasp for every ounce of air as you concentrate on scaling this danger
mountain.  You can't rest now, the sooner you get to your destination the
better, for who knows what kind of unpredicatable weather could occur up on
this part of the region.

rooms.Name: The Great Mountain of Norn
rooms.Description:
The windy conditions up on this mountain is unbearable.  It's cold and dry
up in this altitude and there doesn't seem to be a ledge in sight that you
can rest on.  You must rely on your strength in order to reach your goal
and that's asking a lot from your ailing body.

rooms.Name: The Great Mountain of Norn
rooms.Description:
There are not many who came back from scaling this mammoth mountain, at
least not the live ones.  Only a fool would climb a mountain with rough
edges and loose crevices.  This entire mountain is so unstable that it
looks as though it would collapse in a heavy storm.

rooms.Name: On top of the Great Mountain of Norn
rooms.Description:
The cold winds up on this mountain is as strong as a mini-hurricane, but
that doesn't seem to affect the old man sitting on the rock.  He's just
sitting there, singing his song and at the same time drinking from a large
barrel.  He looks too drunk to acknowledge your presence but that doesn't
mean he's vulnerable to attacks.  This old man is the size of three men and
from his armored gear and his oversized bloodaxe, he looks like he could
fight an entire army!

rooms.Name: On top of the Great Mountain of Norn
rooms.Description:
You are dismay to see that there's nothing on top of this great mountain,
except for an old man sitting on a rock.  He seems to be singing a tune in
a foreign language that you're not familiar with.  It might not be wise to
get closer to him for he looks pretty big and strong even for a man of his
age.  There's nowhere else to go except back down from where you came.

rooms.Name: The Great Mountain of Norn
rooms.Description:
The frigid wind from the east is just unrelenting and you're about to pass
out from this extreme condition.  But as you start drifting towards
unconsciousness, you notice the cliff is right above you.  Now if you could
summon just an ounce of strength, you might be able to finish your climb.

rooms.Name: The Great Mountain of Norn
rooms.Description:
You're at the half-way point of this mountain and you still have several
miles to scale before you could get to the top.  The cold frosty wind
blowing from the east is beginning to numb your rough hands.  You feel
you're about to fall soon if you don't find a small ledge to rest on.

rooms.Name: Into the bottomless pit of darkness...
rooms.Description:
You scream for help but there's no one here that can save you from this
horrible fate.  Where will this pit end, you wonder to yourself.  As you
continue your descent to wherever this hell hole takes you, you can feel
the cold draft of this tunnel brush against you.  If you don't fall anytime
soon, the sub-zero conditions will surely take your life before then.
Sorry, young adventurer, your time has come...see you in the next life.

Exits.Description: This exit will take you back home if you actually survived this DT.

rooms.Name: On the ledge inside the Mountain of Norn
rooms.Description:
As you reach this ledge on the side of the cliff, the first thing you
notice is the man that's sleeping on the ground.  He must be under a spell,
for why else would a man sleep inside a mountain, on a ledge next to a pit
of eternal darkness?  As you observe this husky bearded man, you can see
that he's wearing armor all around his massive body and a thick fur cloak
that shields him from the cold winds.  His hands seem to be keeping a firm
grip of a large broadsword.  Though this man is sleeping, he doesn't look
peaceful and in fact, he looks quite angry and disturbed even in slumber.

Exits.Description: You wonder where this bottomless pit will take you...
You wonder where this bottomless pit will take you...
You wonder where this bottomless pit will take you...

rooms.Name: Climbing precariously on the side of a cliff...
rooms.Description:
Sweat is flowing down your brow like a dripping faucet.  Your foolish
curiosity might be the death of you.  You are just barely gripping the
small crevices on the edge of this cliff and the rocks aren't stable enough
to ensure that you'll get a firm hold of your position.  The pit of 
darkness is just waiting patiently to engulf you...

Exits.Description: You wonder where this bottomless pit will take you...
You wonder where this bottomless pit will take you...
You wonder where this bottomless pit will take you...

rooms.Name: The end of the tunnel inside the Mountain of Norn
rooms.Description:
Luckily the cold wind from the north kept you from stepping over the cliff.
You could've fallen into that dark bottomless pit where no one would have
ever find your body.  As you look over the cliff, you'll notice a man
dressed in viking gears is sleeping on a small ledge.

Exits.Description: You wonder where this bottomless pit will take you...

rooms.Name: A tunnel inside the Mountain of Norn
rooms.Description:
This dark and dank passageway is taking you deeper into the heart of this
mountain.  Who knows what might lurk inside this secret tunnel, it has been
untouched for a millenium.  As you continue your journey northward, you 
notice a cold wind is blowing at you from that direction.

rooms.Name: A tunnel inside the Mountain of Norn
rooms.Description:
You can't imagine who could had cut through this steel-hard rock and built
an entire tunnel.  It's dark in here and you can barely see where you're
headed.  You can't even hear a sound coming from anywhere, not even the
bats that are sleeping atop of you.

Exits.Description: This exit will take you back to the outside of this great mountain.

rooms.Name: The Great Mountain of Norn
rooms.Description:
The strong winds of the east is blowing hard at your face.  You're cold and
unshielded from this harsh condition.  As you struggle to climb every inch
of this cold stone mountain, you notice a round-shaped rock located north of
you and there seems to be some inscriptions carved onto it.

ExtraDescs.Description:
"...the Mightiest of vikings is kept here and only a fool would disturb his
 one-thousand year sleep..."

rooms.Name: The Great Mountain of Norn
rooms.Description:
There doesn't seem to be anything intelligent living on this mountain.
Only mountain goats and snow leopards would dare live in this precarious
enviroment.  The climb continues upwards and you're not even close to the
half-way point of this colossal mountain.

rooms.Name: The Great Mountain of Norn
rooms.Description:
This is not good.  You are already tired from all this climbing.  The long
and tiresome journey from the snowy trail has finally taken its toll.
There's about several miles of this mountain to scale before you can reach
the top of it.  You'll be lucky if you even reach the half-way point.

rooms.Name: On a snowy trail
rooms.Description:
You can see that you're getting closer to one of the great mountains of the
north.  That mountain stands much taller than Mt. Everest and looks as
beautiful as the picturesque Mt. Fuji.  The snowy trail ends here and
there's nowhere you can go except back to where you came...or climb up this
mammoth rock!

rooms.Name: On a snowy trail
rooms.Description:
This path seems to be turning towards the north again, to the great 
mountains of that region.  The snow is still thick as ever and it's getting
impossible to move along this trail.  With only your strength and
determination to survive, you hope that's enough to get you to your
destination point...wherever that may be.

rooms.Name: On top of Mountain Nobul
rooms.Description:
The statue that stands before you is truly the ugliest statue you have ever
seen.  Its face could scare away even the bravest of warriors and its 
freakish stare is enough to send chills down your spine.  There's something
mystical about this statue and as you get closer to observe it, you notice
the statue figure seems to be drooling...

rooms.Name: On top of Mountain Nobul
rooms.Description:
There doesn't seem to be anyone on top of this mountain except for you but
as you look towards to a large boulder, you notice an ugly gargoyle-like 
statue standing there.  It looks almost alive...but you hesitate to walk
towards it because of the fear that it might not be a statue after all.

rooms.Name: On top of Mountain Nobul
rooms.Description:
You are relieved to know that you've made it to the top of this mountain.
As you struggle to climb off the side of the cliff, you are in awe to see
the beauty of the landscape that surrounds this island.  The weather from
the stormy waters that you came from is nowhere in sight and you breathe a
sigh of relief as you lay down to rest your tired body.

rooms.Name: Climbing up the Mountain Nobul
rooms.Description:
Your fingers and hands are bloodied from all this climbing and you dare not
stop now, for a fall at this altitude will certainly kill you.  There are
still a lot of mountain to scale but you sense you're getting closer and
closer to the top.

rooms.Name: Climbing up the Mountain Nobul
rooms.Description:
This mountain is made of the strongest and thickest granite.  As you
continue your climbing upwards, you'll notice the powdery sand from the
crevices is causing you to lose grip.  You feel like you're about to fall
off this mountain if you don't hang on with both your hands.

rooms.Name: On a small remote island
rooms.Description:
You've landed on a strange island where a tall mountain covers its entire
surface.  There doesn't seem to be a path that'll take you up there so
scaling this mountain is your only option to get anywhere.  This mountain is
more than two hundred feet tall and it'll take a day before you can reach
the summit.

rooms.Name: The stormy waters of Lake Elric
rooms.Description:
The deadly storm doesn't seem to be dying out anytime soon, and you feel
your arms are beginning to tire from all this paddling.  Fortunately for
you, there's a small island to the west of here.  It's the only land that
you can see anywhere around this god-forsaken place.

Exits.Description:
There's something mystical about that small island in the middle of this
lake.

rooms.Name: The stormy waters of Lake Elric
rooms.Description:
You're choking in sea water as you struggle to stay about the surface.
There's no one here that can help you and even if they were here, there's
no way they can save you.  The hellish waters of Lake Elric is just too
brutal and it'll be a matter of minutes before you get thrashed by the
waves and into unconsciousness.

rooms.Name: The stormy waters of Lake Elric
rooms.Description:
Your boat is pushed back and forth and there's no way you can make it out
of this lake alive!  The frce of the storm is just too awesome and not
even your great strength could endure the conditions of this magnitude.
You struggle but you know only the greatest of warriors can make it to the
other side of this lake.

Exits.Description: This exit will take you back to the snowy trail which you came from.

rooms.Name: On a snowy trail
rooms.Description:
As you reach this section of the snowy trail, you'll notice a lake of
darkness to the southwest of here.  The strange dark clouds that cover
this lake looks very threatening and if you're smart, you would not try
to swim or take you boat in there.

Exits.Description:
This is the port to Lake Elric which is just southwest of here.  The stormy
waters of that Lake looks awfully intimidating....

rooms.Name: On a snowy trail
rooms.Description:
This long path is taking you west and east of here and you have no idea
where it will lead you to.  You are tired and your legs are about to
collapse but you know you must endure at least till you see the end of this
endless snow trail.

rooms.Name: On a snowy trail
rooms.Description:
Your legs are just in terrible shape as you struggle in this thick snow bed.
There seems to be no sign of intelligent life anywhere on this region
except for small harmless mammals and some birds flying in the sky.  There
are a few vegetations around this area but nothing edible.

rooms.Name: On a snowy trail
rooms.Description:
You wonder to yourself where exactly does this long trail will take you.
It seems to be leading you towards the northern mountains but then it
takes you elsewhere.  You wonder if this path will even lead you anywhere,
or maybe there's a cleverly concealed deathtrap at its end!

rooms.Name: On a snowy trail
rooms.Description:
If not for the shade of those great northern mountains, your skin would be
blistered by the sun.  The snow from your waist-down is thick as ever 
forcing you to move at a very slow pace.  The northern mountains are still
too far away, it'll probably be nightfall before you can reach there.

rooms.Name: On a snowy trail
rooms.Description:
As you move further along this path, you'll notice it gets harder and 
harder to breathe.  As you go further northwards, you can see this entire
area is shifted upwards toward those snowy mountains.  So as you advance
closer to the mountainous region, be prepare to gasp for air.

rooms.Name: On a snowy trail
rooms.Description:
This long path seems to be leading you to nowhere.  But you know you have
to keep moving until you find something that could get you out of this icy-
cold weather.  If the small hare and the white-tailed deer could survive
this harsh condition then so can you.

rooms.Name: The altar of the Golden Temple
rooms.Description:
As you reach the altar of this temple, you'll notice a man is standing here
reciting chants from a book.  He's cloaked in a dark ragged cloth and his
face is concealed by a hood.  The old man does not sense your presence, or
probably he just doesn't care.  You sense this stranger is someone of great
power and if he gets aggravated, you can't imagine what he will do to you.
The book on his table looks like a spell book of some sort and it seems to
emit an illuminating aura around it.

rooms.Name: Inside the Golden Temple of Nemesis
rooms.Description:
You gasp as you look at everything that are around you.  The walls, the
furnishings, and the floors are all covered in solid gold.  The size of this
temple is almost that of the Roman Cathedral and possibly much bigger.  You
wonder who lives in this temple and what purpose is it used for.  This 
temple looks like an abbey or a grand museum.

Exits.Description: This gates will take you back outside of this Golden Temple!

rooms.Name: In front of a golden temple
rooms.Description:
You are in awe to see such an incredible monument.  This entire structure
is covered in solid gold as well as the floor that surrounds it.  You are
curious to know what's inside this temple but a guard stands in your way.
He doesn't look at you nor does he acknowledges your presence.  You are
only a pesky bug that could be easily squashed if you annoy him too much.

Exits.Description: These doors will take you inside the Golden Temple of Nemesis!

rooms.Name: On a snowy trail
rooms.Description:
The surroundings of this section of the trail is very relaxing to the eyes
because the shade of the northern snowy mountains.  The snow is not as
blinding as it was when you came into this parts of the trail.  As you walk
further along this path, you'll notice a large golden temple is built
northeast of here.

rooms.Name: On a snowy trail
rooms.Description:
As soon as you walk into this section of the trail, a loud roar nearly
breaks your eardrums.  Before you, stands the biggest, the ugliest, and the
hungriest monster of this snowy region.  This beast looks as though it came
from hell because of its devilish-looking horns and its two evil red eyes.
He moves on two elongated limbs and an extended spiked tail.  This creature
is about to attack you with his long flexible tentacles and there's nowhere
you can escape!

rooms.Name: On a snowy trail
rooms.Description:
Walking through a snow bed is next to impossible especially when it's four
feet deep.  You struggle as you try to move at a faster pace.  The quicker
you find shelter now, there's a good chance you might survive the next
blizzard storm.

rooms.Name: On a snowy trail
rooms.Description:
There is not one place here that's not covered in snow and you wonder how
you will find shelter if a blizzard comes suddenly.  This snowy trail seems
to be divided into two paths, the northeast and the south direction.  Both
trails look harmless but who knows where they will take you...

rooms.Name: On a snowy trail
rooms.Description:
You are tired and hungry from this long journey but there's no way you can
catch a hare in this thick snow bed.  You'll have to depend on your food
sources that you brought to here.  There's nothing unusual about this
section of the trail as it continues east and southwest of here.

rooms.Name: On top of the rock formation
rooms.Description:
As you reach the top of this large rock, the first thing you notice is a
bearded man sitting down with his legs crossed.  He looks pretty big and
mean.  With a large double-edged broadsword by his side and a shield spiked
with razor-edged shards, this man must be a warrior of some sort.  The
horned helm that he wears on top of his head makes him look fierce and 
intimidating.  He doesn't sense your presence for now so just carefully
climb back down this rock before it's too late.

rooms.Name: A large natural rock formation
rooms.Description:
This tall cold slab of rock was recently formed by a shift in the earth's
crust.  Its dark slippery surface looks as though it was cut apart by a
sharp butter knife.  As you try scaling this colossal formation, you find
it hard to keep your footing.  The surface is so smooth, it's as though the
entire rock was covered in oil.

rooms.Name: On a snowy trail
rooms.Description:
This path seems to stop here but to the east of here, there's a strange
rock formation that'll take you up to the top of the surface cliff.  It
looks pretty dangerous to climb up there but who cares, it would be much
drier up there and you can rest on the top surface.

rooms.Name: On a snowy trail
rooms.Description:
The snow is beginning to thicken on this section of the trail.  You are now
chest-high in snow and you wonder if you should walk back to the other
direction.  You struggle as you try to make your way through this snowy
obstacle but it seems almost impossible to move in this bed of thick snow.

rooms.Name: On a snowy trail
rooms.Description:
There's nothing special about this section of the snowy trail.  Everything
here is quiet, still, and untouched.  The only living things you see here
are a snow bunny hopping around in search of plants and some birds circling
in the skies above.

rooms.Name: On a snowy trail
rooms.Description:
As you wander along this trail, you'll notice it splits into two
directions.  The path to the southeast looks tranquil and deserted much
like the rest of this trail.  The passage north of here seems to lead
towards the snowy mountains.

rooms.Name: On a snowy trail
rooms.Description:
The mountains here are just magnificent and you can't help but to admire
its natural beauty.  You wonder where is this strange land located on the
map but it doesn't seem to be anywhere on the charts.  You're probably
somewhere in northern Europe, a place where nomadic settlers keep away from
because of extreme temperatures.

rooms.Name: On a snowy trail
rooms.Description:
The temperature in this strange land is way below zero degrees.  You wonder
who could live in such horrid conditions.  Only animals and savage sub-
human barbarians coul endure this hellish weather.  The waist-high snow
covered trail continues northeast of here.

rooms.Name: On a snowy trail
rooms.Description:
The snow is about waist-deep and it's getting deeper as you walk further
along this trail.  Everywhere you look, there are mountains and small
bushes covered in snow.  It's not exactly a place you would want to live
but the landscapes here would make a great tourist attraction.

rooms.Name: The abode of Gorg, Last of the Cavemen
rooms.Description:
The smell in this section of the cavern is just unbearable.  As you adjust
your eyes in this darkness, you can see a figure of a man/ape entity
standing in front of you.  You can hear his heavy breathing and his knuckles
crackling as though he's about to smash someone's face in...probably 
yours...  You have invaded his home and now you must face the consequences
of your curiosity.  Prepare to die, evolved human scum.

rooms.Name: Inside a dark bear cave
rooms.Description:
Darkness surrounds you as quickly as a sudden blizzard storm.  You wonder
who (or what) could live inside this dark, smelly cavern so you begin
looking around here.  On the walls of this cavern, there are primitive
paintings that are drawn by prehistoric men, hundreds of thousands of years
old.  On the ground, there are stone utensils lying there...but these tools
seem to be made just recently.  This indicates that there's someone living
inside this cave...

rooms.Name: On a snowy trail
rooms.Description:
You are in awe to see the beautiful landscapes of this countryside.  The
snowy mountains are just magnificent and the air, though it's harder to
breathe in this altitude, is so fresh and clean.  To the west of here, 
there's a dark bear cave...

rooms.Name: On a snowy trail
rooms.Description:
The blizzard storm from the southeast is absent from this part of the
trail.  However, this area is still covered in blinding white snow and the
path that took you to this place is almost completely buried in snow.  The
snowy trail seems to split in two, one path leading to the west and the
other to the southeast.

rooms.Name: On a snowy trail, in a blizzard storm
rooms.Description:
The storm seems to be dying down but it's still very strong.  You're
shivering and in dire need of a warn fire and shelter.  There's no one
around this area that can help you.  The only way you can get out of here
is to depend on your own determination to survive.

rooms.Name: On a snowy trail, in a blizzard storm
rooms.Description:
You can feel the powerful wind and the heavy snow hitting at your face so
hard that you squeal in pain.  There's no way anyone can survive another
hour in this turbulence, only a fool would continue this futile journey
into nothingness.

rooms.Name: On a snowy trail, in a blizzard storm
rooms.Description:
The weather conditions on this snowy trail is just plain harsh.  Your
fingers are beginning to numb and your toes feel as though they're about to
snap right off.  The blizzard storm is so blinding that not even an expert
ranger could find his way around here.

rooms.Name: A narrow path inside the forest
rooms.Description:
This forest is more than just any forest, it's a deathtrap for any
journeyman who dare enter this wooded area.  However, this forest seems
to end here as you see a new trail that'll take you to a strange world.
To the northeast of here, you can see a snowy trail...there seem to be a
blizzard storm happening there...  How odd, you wonder to yourself.  In
this forest it's hot and humid and to the northeast, the conditions there
are the complete opposite.

rooms.Name: A narrow path inside the forest
rooms.Description:
The humid conditions of this forest is unbearable but you know you cannot
stop now...the creatures are ready to attack once you slow down.  You are
weary of the stinging bites of the bloodthirsty mosquitoes and leeches.
Your head is spinning and you're about to black out from exhaustion.  This
dark forest looks to end somewhere...you just hope it better be soon...

rooms.Name: A narrow path inside the forest
rooms.Description:
You are getting tired from this journey but you know that if you stop now,
the meat-eating creatures of this forest would find you and eat you alive.
Your tired legs are bloodied by the thorny bushes and the deep gashes from
tripping on above-ground roots.  You are thirsty, tired, and hurt, but
there's nothing you can do about that now except to try and pass through
this humid jungle.

rooms.Name: A narrow path inside the forest
rooms.Description:
There are glowing eyes and strange noises following wherever you go.
Your heart is beginning to pound faster as you sense heavy breathing behind
you.  Something is following you and it sounds vicious.  It's ready to
attack you at any moment, so watch out!

rooms.Name: A narrow path inside the forest
rooms.Description:
How dar can darkness get, you wonder to yourself.  It's so dark that not
even your light-source could show you the right direction to head.  The
forest is beginning to thicken and this path gets more narrower as you walk
further into the heart of the forest.

rooms.Name: A narrow path inside the forest
rooms.Description:
The darkness is forcing you to move at a slow pace as you try to pass
through this forest trail.  Bugs are still swarming around your hot and
sweaty body and they're becoming so annoying that you scream in
frustration.  The forest trail continues west of here.

rooms.Name: A narrow path inside the forest
rooms.Description:
The canopy of the tall redwood trees covers this entire forest ground
making it hard to even see where you're heading.  Trees and bushes are all
around you, and the mosquitoes and all sorts of bugs are flying everywhere
feasting on your exposed flesh.
